<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-38sZ4R_sMBCwiHUFVgbLkg" name=",_oD3RkJZ5EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" guid="-38sZ4R_sMBCwiHUFVgbLkg" changeDate="2011-08-24T04:11:29.459-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The three factors that contribute to an ASIL are:-&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Severity (S):- How severe will the injuries be on a person involved in an accident that occurs as a consequence of a&#xD;
    potential hazard.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Probability of exposure (E):- How likely is such a situation which leads to the hazardous event likely to occur.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Controllability (C):- How much control does the driver or other potential participants have in avoiding the hazardous&#xD;
    event or situation.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For a detailed explanation of this&amp;nbsp;task it is advised that the user refers to ISO 26262, volume 3, clause 7.4.5,&#xD;
    and also&amp;nbsp;Annex B2, examples of severity,&amp;nbsp;and Annex B3 examples of the probability exposure, in Volume 3.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_7ZkIsJZ-EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Estimate potential severity" guid="_7ZkIsJZ-EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    For each hazardous event the severity of the item shall be estimated and assigned to one of the severity classes as&#xD;
    detailed in the table below.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table dir=&quot;ltr&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;4&quot; width=&quot;616&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;12%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>Class&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;12%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>S0&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;21%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>S1&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;27%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>S2&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;28%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>S3&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;12%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Description&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;12%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    No injuries&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;21%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Light and moderate injuries&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;27%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Severe and life-threatening injuries (survival probable)&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;28%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Life-threatening injuries (survival uncertain), fatal injuries&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
For further detail on this section, refer to ISO 26262, volume 3, clause 7.4.5.2 and Annex B2,Examples of&#xD;
severity,&amp;nbsp;&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>&lt;em>Copyright ISO 2011. All rights reserved. Reproduced with permission of ANSI. This is a draft ISO Standard&#xD;
    that is subject to change without notice and cannot be referred to or relied upon as a final ISO&#xD;
    standard.&lt;/em>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_-RcUwJZ-EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Estimate probability of exposure in operational situations" guid="_-RcUwJZ-EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    For&amp;nbsp;each operational situation the probability of exposure shall be estimated and assigned to one of the&#xD;
    probability&amp;nbsp;classes as detailed in the table below.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The difference in probability from one E classification to the next is an order of magnitude.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table dir=&quot;ltr&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;4&quot; width=&quot;657&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;15%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>Class&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>E0&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>E1&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>E2&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>E3&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>E4&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;15%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Description&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Incredible&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Very low probability&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Low probability&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Medium probability&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;17%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    High probability&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
It should be noted that E0 may be used for those situations that are suggested during hazard and risk analysis, but which&#xD;
are considered to be extremely unusual, or incredible and therefore not followed up. A rationale shall be available for the&#xD;
exclusion of these situations. If a hazard is assigned to exposure class E0, no ASIL assignment is required.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For further detail on this section, refer to ISO 26262, volume 3, clause 7.4.5.3, and annex&amp;nbsp;B3 Examples of the&#xD;
    probability of exposure.&amp;nbsp;These clauses&amp;nbsp;give detailed guidance on some of the&amp;nbsp;considerations that need to&#xD;
    be taken into account when determining the probability of exposure.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>&lt;em>Copyright ISO 2011. All rights reserved. Reproduced with permission of ANSI. This is a draft ISO Standard&#xD;
    that is subject to change without notice and cannot be referred to or relied upon as a final ISO&#xD;
    standard.&lt;/em>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_EGHpIJZ_EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Estimate controllability" guid="_EGHpIJZ_EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The controllability of each hazardous event, by the driver or other traffic participants, shall be estimated. The&#xD;
    controllability shall be assigned to one of the controllability classes C0, C1, C2 and C3 in accordance with Table3.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table dir=&quot;ltr&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;2&quot; cellpadding=&quot;4&quot; width=&quot;643&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;11%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>Class&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;21%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>C0&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;18%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>C1&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;19%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>C2&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;30%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>C3&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;11%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Description&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;21%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Controllable in general&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;18%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Simply controllable&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;19%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Normally controllable&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td height=&quot;19&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;30%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
                    Difficult to control or uncontrollable&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
For further detail on this section, refer to ISO 26262, volume 3, clause 7.4.5.4 which gives detailed guidance on some of&#xD;
the&amp;nbsp;considerations that need to be taken into account when determining the controllability.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>&lt;em>Copyright ISO 2011. All rights reserved. Reproduced with permission of ANSI. This is a draft ISO Standard&#xD;
    that is subject to change without notice and cannot be referred to or relied upon as a final ISO&#xD;
    standard.&lt;/em>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>To determine the values for the factors that are used to define an items ASIL</purpose>
